The expansion of Polesine since 1484. The yellow area of the territory of Polesine, established in 1484 within the land of the Venetian Republic after the Ferrara War, is marked in yellow. The areas marked in red are part of the areas that were separated from the state of the Church in 1815 and merged with Polesine to form the province of Rovigo, part of the Kingdom of Lombardy-Venice. Other areas separated from the church state in 1815, which were originally annexed to the province of Venice of the same kingdom, are marked in green. The green and green areas were separated from the province of Venice in 1851 and merged with the province of Rovigo
